  "description": "PerceiveImagine is an EEG dataset capturing neural activity during visual perception and imagery tasks. Participants viewed images for 6 seconds following a prompt, then closed their eyes and imagined the same images for 6 seconds. This dataset enables investigation of neural correlates underlying the transition between visual perception and mental imagery.",
